Don&#39;t round the actual value.  Let [System.out.printf()](https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/17/docs/api/java.base/java/io/PrintStream.html#printf(java.lang.String,java.lang.Object...)) do the work for you.
```
double [] data = {1.4452, 123.223,23.229};
for (double v : data) {
   System.out.printf(&quot;%.2f%n&quot;,v);
}
```
prints
```
1.45
123.22
23.23

There are multiple ways to do this.

`Math.round()`
```java
double i = 2.3333;
System.out.println(Math.round(i*100) / 100);
```

`NumberFormat.format()`
```java
NumberFormat formatter = new DecimalFormat(&quot;#0.00&quot;);     
System.out.println(formatter.format(2.3333));
```

`System.out.printf()`
```java
System.out.printf(&quot;%.2f&quot;, 3.2222);
```

Probaly there are 10 more ways of doing it, thats just what I can think of right now.

